.TH "phy_prepare_link" 9 "phy_prepare_link" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
phy_prepare_link \- prepares the PHY layer to monitor link status
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" phy_prepare_link
.BI "(struct phy_device *phydev "  ","
.BI "void (*handler)(struct net_device *) "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phydev" 12
target phy_device struct
.IP "handler" 12
callback function for link status change notifications
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Tells the PHY infrastructure to handle the
gory details on monitoring link status (whether through
polling or an interrupt), and to call back to the
connected device driver when the link status changes.
If you want to monitor your own link state, don't call
this function.
